article.description: Akwasi Yeboah scored 16 points, Lucas Woodhouse added 14 and Stony Brook beat Lehigh 62-57 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Woodhouse makes 12 FTs, helps Stony Brook beat Lehigh 62-57
article.linkText: Woodhouse makes 12 FTs, helps Stony Brook beat Lehigh 62-57
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Akwasi Yeboah scored 16 points, Lucas Woodhouse added 14 and Stony Brook beat Lehigh 62-57 on Tuesday night. Yeboah was 6 of 13 from the field and made three 3-pointers. Woodhouse made just 1 of 8 field goals but was 12 of 12 from the line. Stony Brook (3-5) shot 32 percent from the floor on 19-of-60 shooting, but made 17 of 19 free throws. Tim Kempton had 27 points to lead Lehigh (3-5). The game was tied at 39-39 with about 12 minutes left. The Seawolves used a 10-1 spurt and led 49-40. Tyrell Sturdivant scored five points during the stretch. Lehigh chipped away, and pulled to 58-57 on Kahron Ross's 3-pointer with 37 seconds remaining. Woodhouse made a pair of free throws, Lehigh's Kyle Leufroy missed a 3-point shot, and Woodhouse made two more from the line to end it.
